I am a late-comer to the Law & Order phenomenon.  I didn't get interested in the show until about six months ago and now I have made it through season 10. I love the plot lines and the characters on the show. I don't think you have to start with season 1 but I did find it helpful that I learned about Olivia and Elliot a lot in the first season. A part of me was worried that the plots would get redundant but they never do  Each episode has such a diverse range of supporting actors and actresses that they keep the show lively and entertaining. Definitely recommend buying the DVD series for people who have seen the series before and for those who have never seen it before.

I ordered this episode specifically because it deals with FASD.  While I appreciate there being an episode of a prime time TV show that took on what is a very complex issue I wish that it had dealt with more than how FASD affects the parents - children born with FASD become adults with FASD.  This topic has so much more to consider than just the prevention message they zeroed in on.

I love that the officers in the show are "good" cops, as opposed to some of the characters on some other shows,The characters are firmly ethical, and complex enough to be human. As a teacher of at-risk children, I identify with the heartbreak and its toll on people's lives. Yay! Good wins!

I really enjoy the program and the season. I gave it only 2 stars because I purchased season 5 when it was available as streaming video, and 1 month later it was pulled from availability by Amazon. Now when I try to watch, the message Watch thru Hulu comes up. ( but you only can do THAT if you have a membership WITH Hulu.) There should be information someplace to indicate how long Amazon will carry a program so that those of us who purchase streaming video can decide if it is worth it. DVDs don't disappear from your shelves when they are no longer carried.
